==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Styrolene
<hw>Sty"ro*lene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>An unsaturated hydrocarbon, <chform>C8H8</chform>, obtained by the
distillation of storax, by the decomposition of cinnamic acid, and by
the condensation of acetylene, as a fragrant, aromatic, mobile liquid;
-- called also <altname>phenyl ethylene</altname>, <altname>vinyl
benzene</altname>, <altname>styrol</altname>,
<altname>styrene</altname>, and <altname>cinnamene</altname>.</def><--
most commonly, styrene -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Styrone</ent>⟦br⟧
